originalText.text:
I joined right when it opened and have signature membership. It's good for a quick workout before work. It's not as big or even well appointed as the dumbo location or for any other lifetime I've been at across the country. I really like Lifetime but I wouldn't promote this location to anyone.

My biggest complaint here is the dressing room. It's warmer inside the men's dressing room than it is outside when it was 90+ degrees out. Most of us go there before work and get dressed  for the office. However, 90% of the people I see leave dripping sweat. The first comment I got back was "people like to burn extra calories" which doesn't seem at all reasonable to me (you burn an extra calorie or two in exchange to leave dripping sweat and overheated).

I've mentioned this and other possible small changes to improve the user experience. No one followed up with me and when I asked what was the feedback from management all the employee said was its not something they can do. Again, these were very reasonable and easy suggestions (slightly cooler in locker rooms, having sufficient small towels, have a clean lifting area).

Again, I would advise people if they do want to join Lifetime to go to other locations and you may be more impressed.

originalText.text: My partner and I switched to Life Time from Equinox and it was the best decision we ever made! Justin, our client advisor, greets us every day with a smile and warm welcome and the rest of the staff are awesome as well. The facilities are well kept and there's enough room so that you don’t feel like it's crowded, even during peek hours.

originalText.text: I’ve been to fair share of gym in manhattan and recently retired from equinox. This place makes me feel positive energy and welcomed. Even the maintenance staff are friendly unlike equinox, I think that goes to show what type of company Lifetime is.

originalText.text:
This gym is overall really small for Life Time,
and the AC doesn’t work well. Very difficult to shower and go to work when you’re still sweating. They had just one set of each weight for free weights, and it was very hard to find room to lift, even with very few members around. Just a few filled the space!  The staff was super nice though - I feel for them that they are at such a subpar location. Many issues are building issues (AC, leaking windows, etc) , but life time chose the tiny space.
